outputs.output_descr:
Project BRA/12/013 aims at strengthening access to justice. The Project`s main goals are: 1) The establishment of a mechanism of social participation for effective decision making; 2) Planning and monitoring of public policies on access to justice in order to put into question the central concepts of this subject; 3) Build channels of communication between the various actors that permeate the justice system; 4) Promote a new institutional culture open to dialogue between state and civil society; 5) promote alternative forms of dispute resolution, and define the principles and guidelines of the National Access to Justice.
To achieve the objectives described, the project is structured into four major results:
1) 1st. National Conference on Access to Justice held;
2) Programme "Dialogues on Justice" developed;
3) Alternative means of resolving conflicts spread and strengthened.
4) Efficient management of the Project.
